{
  "text": "The piezoelectric-patched finite element blade models were also built to simulate the open circuit and short circuit cases as a function of the rotor speed. Models were used to obtain the first bending frequencies as a function of the rotor speed for open circuit and short circuit, respectively. For our rotating piezoelectric finite element blade model simulations, electromechanical coupling coefficient, k 31 , was 0.34, resulting in the short circuit stiffness being 88.4 percent of the open circuit stiffness. The stiffness of Smart Material Corp.'s piezoelectric patch used in this study was 4.395×10 6 psi and 3.887×10 [CITATION_1] psi for open circuit and short circuit, respectively, along the fiber direction. From this finite element modeling approach, the generalized electromechanical coupling coefficients, K 31 , were obtained as a function of the rotor speed using Equation (10). oc sc",
